## Installation

### Install with Ansible Galaxy

```shell
ansible-galaxy install {{role_docs_vars['github_account']}}.{{rolename}}
```

Basic usage is:

```yaml
- hosts: all
  roles:
    - role: {{role_docs_vars['github_account']}}.{{rolename}}
```

### Install with git

If you do not want a global installation, clone it into your `roles_path`.

```shell
git clone git@github.com:{{role_docs_vars['github_account']}}/ansible-{{rolename}}.git /path/to/roles_path
```

But I often add it as a submdule in a given `playbook_dir` repository.

```shell
git submodule add git@github.com:{{role_docs_vars['github_account']}}/ansible-{{rolename}}.git <playbook_dir>/roles/{{rolename}}
```

As the role is not managed by Ansible Galaxy, you do not have to specify the
github user account.

Basic usage is:

```yaml
- hosts: all
  roles:
  - role: {{rolename}}
```
